<h1>A Project Report On “Technical Recruiter Platform”</h1>
<hr />
<h2>CHAPTER 1: Introduction</h2>
<h3>1.1 Background</h3>
<p>The recruitment and hiring process has long been one of the most resource-intensive activities for organizations. Traditionally, human resources (HR) professionals and technical recruiters have had to manually sift through hundreds of resumes for a single job posting, looking for specific skills, experiences, and qualifications. This manual screening is not only time-consuming but also prone to human bias and errors. Furthermore, conducting preliminary technical interviews for numerous candidates requires significant effort from technical teams, diverting them from their core development tasks. </p>
<p>With the advent of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and modern web technologies, the recruitment landscape is undergoing a digital transformation. Automated Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) emerged to solve the resume parsing problem but often rely on rigid keyword matching, leading to qualified candidates being unjustly rejected. </p>
<p>In response to these challenges, the <strong>Technical Recruiter Platform</strong> is designed as an intelligent, AI-powered hiring ecosystem that bridges the gap between companies and job seekers. It features a dual-portal system for HR professionals and Candidates, leveraging AI to semantically match candidates to job descriptions based on their uploaded resumes. Furthermore, it incorporates an automated technical interview module that conducts and scores preliminary interviews, providing AI-generated feedback to both the candidate and the recruiter. This ensures a fair, efficient, and highly streamlined hiring process.</p>
<h3>1.2 Objective</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Automate Resume Screening:</strong> Utilize AI parsing to extract skills and experience from candidate resumes and match them against HR-defined Job Descriptions (JDs).</li>
<li><strong>Facilitate Automated Interviews:</strong> Create a structured digital interview room where candidates answer technical questions, and AI evaluates their responses.</li>
<li><strong>Streamline HR Workflow:</strong> Provide a comprehensive HR Dashboard where recruiters can post jobs, view applicant tracking data, and see automated candidate rankings.</li>
<li><strong>Enhance Candidate Experience:</strong> Offer candidates an intuitive portal to track their applications, take preliminary interviews at their convenience, and receive constructive AI feedback.</li>
<li><strong>Minimize Human Bias:</strong> Rely on data-driven semantic matching and objective AI scoring for initial screening rounds.</li>
</ul>
<h3>1.3 Purpose</h3>
<p>The purpose of the Technical Recruiter Platform is to revolutionize the hiring pipeline by reducing the time-to-hire and improving the quality of candidate screening. By offering an intelligent system that automatically evaluates technical competencies before direct human intervention, the platform ensures that human interviewers only spend time with candidates who genuinely meet the technical baseline for the role. </p>
<h3>1.4 Scope</h3>
<p>The Technical Recruiter Platform caters to HR departments, technical recruiters, and job candidates. Key features and areas of operation include:
* <strong>Job Posting &amp; Management:</strong> HR can create dynamic Job Descriptions specifying required skills and requirements.
* <strong>Candidate Profiling:</strong> Candidates can register, upload resumes, and let the system automatically build their skill profile.
* <strong>Intelligent Candidate Matching:</strong> AI algorithms compare candidate profiles against active JDs and provide a match score.
* <strong>Automated Interview Rooms:</strong> Candidates participate in timed technical interviews.
* <strong>AI Evaluation &amp; Feedback:</strong> The system calculates a total score based on the candidate's answers and generates qualitative feedback.</p>
<h3>1.5 Applicability</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>For Tech Companies &amp; HR Agencies:</strong> Provides a scalable way to filter thousands of applicants based on actual technical merit and AI-evaluated initial interviews.</li>
<li><strong>For Job Seekers (Candidates):</strong> Offers a transparent application process where they receive immediate, unbiased feedback on their technical interviews, helping them understand their standing and areas for improvement.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>CHAPTER 2: Survey</h2>
<h3>2.1 Literature Survey</h3>
<p><strong>1) Traditional Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS)</strong><br />
Traditional ATS software revolutionised hiring by digitizing resumes and tracking candidates through the hiring pipeline. However, most legacy systems rely purely on strict keyword matching. This often leads to the "black hole" effect, where highly qualified candidates are rejected simply because their resume did syntax-variations of the target keywords rather than exact matches. Our platform addresses this by utilizing modern AI to perform semantic matching rather than rigid string matching.</p>
<p><strong>2) Automated Code Assessment Tools</strong><br />
Platforms like HackerRank and LeetCode provide automated technical assessments. While highly effective for algorithms, they heavily focus on competitive programming rather than holistic technical knowledge or domain-specific architectural reasoning. The Technical Recruiter Platform introduces an interactive Q&amp;A style interview that can assess conceptual understanding dynamically alongside coding ability.</p>
<p><strong>3) AI in Human Resources and Sentiment Analysis</strong><br />
The usage of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Large Language Models (LLMs) in HR allows for deep understanding of unstructured data (resumes). Modern research emphasizes using LLMs to read a resume much like a human would, evaluating context, project scope, and experience depth, which this project implements.</p>
<h3>2.2 Survey of Technologies</h3>
<p><strong>1) Frontend Technologies</strong>
* <strong>React:</strong> A declarative, efficient, and flexible JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It allows developers to create large web applications that can change data, without reloading the page.
* <strong>Vite:</strong> A modern frontend build tool that significantly improves the frontend development experience by pre-bundling dependencies and providing ultra-fast Hot Module Replacement (HMR).
* <strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> A utility-first CSS framework that enables rapid UI development. Instead of writing custom CSS, developers use predefined classes to build responsive and modern designs directly within JSX.
* <strong>Framer Motion &amp; Canvas-Confetti:</strong> Libraries used to implement highly interactive and engaging UI animations, improving the overall User Experience (UX) for candidates taking interviews and HR viewing dashboards.</p>
<p><strong>2) Backend Technologies</strong>
* <strong>Python:</strong> A high-level programming language known for its readability and vast ecosystem, making it the industry standard for AI and backend integration.
* <strong>FastAPI:</strong> A modern, fast (high-performance) web framework for building APIs with Python based on standard Python type hints. It provides automatic interactive API documentation and high asynchronous request throughput.
* <strong>Pydantic:</strong> Data validation library used by FastAPI to enforce schema structures, ensuring that data moving between the frontend and database is strictly typed and secure.
* <strong>AI Integration (Generative Models):</strong> Utilized for deep analysis of candidate responses, grading logic, semantic resume parsing, and actionable feedback generation.</p>
<p><strong>3) Database</strong>
* <strong>MongoDB (Motor):</strong> A NoSQL database used for its schema flexibility, making it ideal for storing unstructured data like candidate resumes, dynamic job descriptions, and variable-length interview logs. Motor is the asynchronous Python driver for MongoDB, seamlessly integrating with FastAPI.</p>
<hr />
<h2>CHAPTER 3: Requirement and Analysis</h2>
<h3>3.1 Problem Definition</h3>
<p>In the fast-paced tech industry, companies face a massive influx of applications for every open position. Technical recruiters are burdened with manual resume screening, which takes an average of 3-5 minutes per resume. Additionally, scheduling and conducting first-round technical screening interviews consumes hours of engineering bandwidth. Candidates, on the other hand, suffer from long wait times and often receive generic rejection emails without any actionable feedback. </p>
<p><strong>Proposed Solutions:</strong>
* Automate the initial screening phase using AI-powered resume parsing.
* Implement a structured, digital "Interview Room" that assesses candidates autonomously.
* Provide auto-generated performance feedback to candidates.
* Centralize application tracking and candidate rankings in a clean HR dashboard.</p>
<h3>3.2 Requirement Specification</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Module 1: Authentication &amp; Role Management:</strong> Secure login and registration supporting distinct <code>hr</code> and <code>candidate</code> roles.</li>
<li><strong>Module 2: HR Dashboard &amp; Job Management:</strong> HR users can create, manage, and view JDs. They can track total applicants, active interviews, and candidate rankings.</li>
<li><strong>Module 3: Candidate Portal &amp; Resume Upload:</strong> Candidates can view available jobs, upload their resumes, and have their skills parsed and stored in their profile.</li>
<li><strong>Module 4: Matching Engine:</strong> The backend dynamically calculates the suitability of a candidate for a specific JD.</li>
<li><strong>Module 5: Interview Module:</strong> A timed environment where candidates answer technical questions. The system submits these to the AI service for grading and feedback generation.</li>
</ul>
