</code></pre>
<h2>CHAPTER 4: System Design</h2>
<h3>4.1 Basic Modules</h3>
<p>The system architecture of the Technical Recruiter Platform is primarily divided into the frontend interface, the backend API layer, the database storage layer, and the AI service integration.
1. <strong>Frontend Module (React + Vite):</strong> Handles user interactions, routing, state management (using React Context/Hooks), and displays dynamic data visually through dashboards.
2. <strong>Backend Module (FastAPI):</strong> Serves as the central hub, providing RESTful endpoints. It handles business logic, database queries, and data validation using Pydantic models.
3. <strong>Authentication Module:</strong> Uses hashed passwords (bcrypt) and potentially JWT tokens for securely managing user sessions for both HR and Candidates.
4. <strong>AI Service Module:</strong> Acts as a broker between the FastAPI backend and external Generative AI providers (e.g., OpenAI or Google Gemini API). It parses resumes and generates technical interview questions/evaluations.
5. <strong>Database Module (MongoDB):</strong> Stores persisted data such as user credentials, job descriptions, candidate parsed profiles, and historical interview records.</p>
<h3>4.2 Database Design</h3>
<p><strong>4.2.a ER Diagram</strong></p>
<pre><code>erDiagram
    USER {
        ObjectId id PK
        string email
        string password
        string role &quot;hr | candidate&quot;
        datetime created_at
    }

    JOB_DESCRIPTION {
        ObjectId id PK
        ObjectId hr_id FK
        string title
        string requirements
        array skills
        datetime created_at
    }

    CANDIDATE_PROFILE {
        ObjectId id PK
        string user_id FK
        string full_name
        string resume_text
        string resume_url
        array skills
        float experience_years
        dict matched_jds
    }

    INTERVIEW {
        ObjectId id PK
        string candidate_id FK
        string jd_id FK
        array questions
        float total_score
        string status &quot;pending | completed&quot;
        string ai_feedback
        datetime created_at
    }

    USER ||--o{ JOB_DESCRIPTION : &quot;creates (if HR)&quot;
    USER ||--|| CANDIDATE_PROFILE : &quot;has (if Candidate)&quot;
    JOB_DESCRIPTION ||--o{ INTERVIEW : &quot;has&quot;
    CANDIDATE_PROFILE ||--o{ INTERVIEW : &quot;takes&quot;
</code></pre>
<h3>4.3 Procedural Design</h3>
<p><strong>4.3.a Data Flow Design (DFD) - Level 0 Context Diagram</strong></p>
<pre><code>flowchart TD
    HR([HR User]) --&gt;|Creates JDs &amp; Views Stats| TRP[Technical Recruiter Platform]
    CAND([Candidate User]) --&gt;|Uploads Resume &amp; Takes Interviews| TRP
    TRP --&gt;|Sends Data for Parsing &amp; Grading| AI([AI Parsing &amp; Grading Engine])
    AI --&gt;|Returns Parsed Skills &amp; Interview Scores| TRP
    TRP &lt;--&gt;|Reads &amp; Writes Data| DB[(MongoDB Database)]
</code></pre>
<h3>4.4 Security Issues</h3>
<p>To ensure the integrity and privacy of user and corporate data, the platform implements several security measures:
* <strong>Password Hashing:</strong> User passwords are not stored in plaintext; they are hashed using strong cryptographic algorithms (e.g., bcrypt) before being saved to MongoDB.
* <strong>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC):</strong> Distinct roles (<code>hr</code> and <code>candidate</code>) restrict access. Candidates cannot access the HR candidate pool, and HR users cannot take interviews meant for candidates.
* <strong>CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing):</strong> Configured in FastAPI to ensure that only the trusted Vite frontend can communicate with the backend API.
* <strong>Data Sanitization:</strong> Pydantic models strictly define the types and formats of expected inputs, automatically rejecting invalid or potentially malicious payloads before they hit the database logic.
* <strong>Secure API Keys:</strong> External AI vendor API keys are stored securely in <code>.env</code> files and never exposed to the frontend browser.</p>
