<h2>CHAPTER 6: Conclusion and Future work</h2>
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p>The Technical Recruiter Platform successfully demonstrates how integrating modern web technologies with Generative Artificial Intelligence can drastically streamline the recruitment process. By automating the most tedious aspects—resume screening and initial technical evaluations—the platform eliminates human bottleneck and bias, ensuring candidates are judged purely on merit and technical competency. The use of FastAPI provided a robust, high-performance API perfectly suited for AI workloads, while React and Tailwind CSS ensured a responsive, intuitive interface for both recruiters and job seekers. </p>
<h3>Future Work</h3>
<p>While the current platform is fully functional and meets the initial objectives, there are several avenues for future enhancement:
1. <strong>Video/Audio Interview Support:</strong> Implementing WebRTC to record candidates answering questions verbally, using Speech-to-Text for the AI to analyze communication skills along with technical accuracy.
2. <strong>Proctoring System:</strong> Adding basic browser-lock or tab-tracking during the interview phase to detect potential cheating.
3. <strong>Advanced Analytics Dashboard:</strong> Providing HR with deeper insights, such as time-to-hire metrics, skill gap analysis of the applicant pool, and historical hiring trends using data visualization libraries like Recharts or Chart.js.
4. <strong>Cloud Deployment:</strong> Containerizing the application using Docker and deploying it on scalable cloud infrastructure (e.g., AWS or Google Cloud Run) to handle large enterprise loads.</p>
